    <briefdescription>
<para>Continuously-variable polyphase resampler, CF32 IQ. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Thin adapter over resamp_core (<ref refid="structresamp__state__t" kindref="compound">resamp_state_t</ref>). Exposes a Resampler-prefixed API so the generated ext.c compiles without changes.</para>
<para>Lifecycle: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="Resampler__core_8h_1af60a7fee58d377e6e1994927b71c3a13" kindref="member">Resampler_state_t</ref><sp/>*r<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="Resampler__core_8h_1a5d2186facf840594733cb3bf809b0bcf" kindref="member">Resampler_create</ref>(0.5);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">float</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>complex<sp/>out[4096];</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">size_t</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>n<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="Resampler__core_8h_1a2d91a921eaadce0f41a8dc58bdfdb23b" kindref="member">Resampler_execute</ref>(r,<sp/>in,<sp/>1024,<sp/>out);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="Resampler__core_8h_1abb7eca8445f4084690228db8695c66a5" kindref="member">Resampler_destroy</ref>(r);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Output buffer sizing: execute: allocate <ref refid="Resampler__core_8h_1ac43b8a22e651a6d819b796a2f8053ba1" kindref="member">Resampler_execute_max_out()</ref> samples. execute_ctrl: same. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
